place.name: WOODMANCOTT
place.gazetteerText: WOODMANCOTT, a parish in Basingstoke district, Hants; 4½ miles NE of Mitcheldever r. station, and 8 SW of Basingstoke. Post town, Basingstoke. Acres, 1,396. Real property, £784. Pop., 87. Houses, 13. The living is a vicarage, united with Popham, in the diocese of Winchester. Value, not reported. Patron, Lord Ashburton. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
